<p>Except for a slight differential in 2013, <strong>I=E2=80=99ve consisten=
tly spent less than I=E2=80=99ve earned</strong>.</p>



<p>So have I been traveling in a financially sustainable way? <em>You betch=
a.</em></p>



<p>Has it been synonymous with budget travel? <em>Not particularly.</em></p=
>



<p>Nor was I trying to make it so.</p>



<p>Perhaps the confusion stems from the early years of my travels; I was ea=
rning less, so I had to make do with less. In those years, out of necessity=
, I acquired various budget travel techniques like getting free accommodati=
on. <strong>But a tight budget is not a necessary cornerstone of financiall=
y sustainable travel</strong>).</p>



