<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Money In (Income)</h3>



<p>What money do you have to work with?</p>



<p>Are you traveling for a fixed term on fixed savings? Or are you making t=
ravel a full-time and indefinite lifestyle?</p>



<p>If it=E2=80=99s indefinite, you=E2=80=99ll need a stream of income to su=
pport you. What kind of income is it? Is it passive (eg: rental income, inv=
estment income, or passive business income), or active (eg: a freelance car=
eer or entrepreneurial venture)?</p>



<p>It=E2=80=99s fine if the answers to these questions vary over time; it=
=E2=80=99s simply important to understand what sort of money you=E2=80=99ve=
 got to work with every step of the way.</p>



<p><em>See also:</em><a href=3D"https://www.theprofessionalhobo.com/make-mo=
ney-while-traveling/" data-modified-href=3D"https://www.theprofessionalhobo=
.com/make-money-while-traveling"><em> How to Make Money While Traveling</em=
></a><br><br></p>



<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Money Out (Expenses)</h3>



<p data-slot-rendered-content=3D"true">Your travel expenses depend entirely=
 on your personal travel style, which in turn, depends on a variety of fact=
ors, such as where you choose to travel to, how fast you go, what you plan =
to do, who you=E2=80=99re traveling with, and what kind of lifestyle you wa=
nt to maintain.<br><br></p>
