<p><strong>Why am I traveling?</strong> Are you anticipating all-inclusive =
cruises and vacations in Europe and the Caribbean, or rustic rural home-sta=
ys? Are you on a mission to conquer mountains, or do you want to hit the ba=
ckpacker trail? What is your theme or purpose for travel? Answering this qu=
estion is the biggest determinant of how much money you need to travel, and=
 how your travels will take shape.</p>



<p><strong>Will I maintain a home base and travel from there?</strong> This=
 will cost more than living nomadically. It=E2=80=99s not right or wrong=E2=
=80=A6it just is. I=E2=80=99ve had a few home bases along the way. The loca=
tion of your home base (and associated cost of living) will be a determinin=
g factor.</p>



<p><strong>Do I have ongoing expenses at home? </strong>E.g., loan payments=
, property expenses, family support. It=E2=80=99s all a part of the travel =
budget!</p>



<p data-slot-rendered-content=3D"true"><strong>Where to?</strong> Pay atten=
tion to the cost of living/traveling through those countries. Obviously dev=
eloping countries will be cheaper than places like North America and Wester=
n Europe. But don=E2=80=99t make assumptions; for example, while South Amer=
ica is cheap on the whole, Chile and Argentina can be very expensive. This =
cost of living calculator from <a href=3D"https://www.expatistan.com/cost-o=
f-living/country/comparison" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" data-modifi=
ed-href=3D"https://www.expatistan.com/cost-of-living/country/comparison">Ex=
patistan</a> will help you generally compare living costs abroad; to dive d=
eeper do a search for =E2=80=9Ccost of living + [city/country you=E2=80=99r=
e researching]=E2=80=9D. If you already have a budget in mind and want to s=
ee where it will take you, check out this calculator from <a href=3D"https:=
//www.theearthawaits.com/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" data-modified=
-href=3D"https://www.theearthawaits.com/">The Earth Awaits</a>, which allow=
s you to search based on not only budget and lifestyle, but also your toler=
ance for crime rate and pollution. Lastly, Budget Your Trip aggregates <a h=
ref=3D"https://www.budgetyourtrip.com/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" =
data-modified-href=3D"https://www.budgetyourtrip.com/">average daily costs =
from real travelers</a>.&nbsp;</p>
