<p><strong>How much ground do I want to cover?</strong> If you=E2=80=99re o=
n a fixed-length trip (eg: one year) and a mission to set foot in 50 countr=
ies, you=E2=80=99d better budget for it. The faster you travel, the more mo=
ney you spend. (And quite frankly, <a href=3D"https://www.theprofessionalho=
bo.com/travel-fatigue-and-slowing-down-the-pace-of-travel/" data-modified-h=
ref=3D"https://www.theprofessionalhobo.com/travel-fatigue-and-slowing-down-=
the-pace-of-travel">the more exhausting your trip will be</a>).</p>



<p><strong>What am I going to do with my time?</strong> Volunteering can re=
duce your expenses; skydiving won=E2=80=99t.</p>


