<h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading"><br>Income Questions</h3>



<p>Beyond the simple =E2=80=9Cdo I have an income or not=E2=80=9D question,=
 lies the following more specific questions. Some of these questions will h=
elp you determine how much money you=E2=80=99ll need in the bank to start t=
raveling with, even if you plan to earn money along the way.</p>



<p><strong>Do I have a business to provide an income along the way?</strong=
> If so, what do you need =E2=80=93 financially and logistically =E2=80=93 =
to operate this business? This is key to calculating your expenses; <em>if =
you are working every day, you=E2=80=99ll inherently spend less money on do=
ing =E2=80=9Cstuff=E2=80=9D to keep you occupied</em>.</p>



<p data-slot-rendered-content=3D"true"><strong>Am I eligible for a Working =
Holiday Visa?</strong> If you don=E2=80=99t have a <a href=3D"https://www.t=
heprofessionalhobo.com/location-independent/" data-modified-href=3D"https:/=
/www.theprofessionalhobo.com/location-independent">location independent bus=
iness</a> going yet, and you=E2=80=99re under 30, a <a href=3D"https://www.=
theprofessionalhobo.com/make-money-while-traveling/#working-holiday-visa" d=
ata-modified-href=3D"https://www.theprofessionalhobo.com/make-money-while-t=
raveling">Working Holiday Visa</a> gives you the chance to stay in a countr=
y for a year with working rights to apply for any job you can land. Most Wo=
rking Holiday Visa users get jobs in seasonal (ie: picking fruit) or hospit=
ality (ie: serving tables) industries. But if you=E2=80=99re highly qualifi=
ed and want to transfer your skills to another country, this visa will help=
 you get your foot in the door.</p>
