<h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading">Real-Life Management of Travel Budgets and I=
ncome</h2>



<p>Okay, you=E2=80=99ve answered the questions above, and you have a vague =
(or perhaps even specific) sense of what you might spend on your anticipate=
d travels, as well as what you might earn.</p>



<p><em>Now, prepare for it all to get totally messed up. </em></p>



<p>In 2013, =E2=80=9Clife happened=E2=80=9D while I was busy making plans, =
and my expenses that year were 54% higher than any other year of my travels=
, before or since.</p>



<p><strong>Budgets are great, and they do work! But flexibility is even mor=
e important. Be willing to roll with the punches, and change tack when nece=
ssary. </strong></p>



<p data-slot-rendered-content=3D"true">The beautiful thing about a travel l=
ifestyle is that it=E2=80=99s all about you. And you=E2=80=A6.along with wh=
at=E2=80=99s important to you and how you want to live your life=E2=80=A6.w=
ill likely change and evolve as you travel. Just make sure your financial p=
lan is flexible enough to change along with you.<br><br></p>
